Section : Test preparation and notes (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1. Preload the latest images and OOBE.
2. Test UUIT cover 32bit and 64bit , EN and SC with Lenovo OS
3. The test need cover all keyboard devices.
4.Flash the latest BIOS.

5. If project contain RGB Keyboard and normal White light Keyboard,white light Keyboard SKU need test SUBS501_KB_EF_03 Keyboard Backlight Function Test
*Note:Fin lighting include TP/ A Logo/Power button/Left D/Right D/Outlet left/Outlet Lighting,If project not support,please skip
 
Section : Lighting Color&Brightness (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

*Please follow the lastest KB lighting SPEC.
*PC Manager/Lenovo vantage/CUE/Lenovo Zone setting priority is greater than FW setting . If PC Manager/Lenovo vantage/CUE/Lenovo Zone is working and SPEC is different from KB lighting SPEC,please follow APP SPEC.
First time "Power on",check the default KB lighting color and lighting mode

Press "Fn" key

Ensure function key LED on and other keys off, LED color is Cool Blue.Function key can refer to Picture 1 in the attachment.


If not support,pls skip; if support,pls follow the lastest KB lighting SPEC.
1.Red
1.1.Change lighting color to red by APP

1.2.Change brightness by APP or Hot Key with 4 level brightness (0, 30%, 60%, 100%)

Ensure OSD show correct and brightness can be changed


OSD follow Project UX SPEC define
2.Green
2.1.Change lighting color to green by APP

2.2.Change brightness by APP or Hot Key with 4 level brightness (0, 30%, 60%, 100%)

Ensure OSD show correct and brightness can be changed


OSD follow Project UX SPEC define
3.Blue
3.1.Change lighting color to blue by APP

3.2.Change brightness by APP or Hot Key with 4 level brightness (0, 30%, 60%, 100%)

Ensure OSD show correct and brightness can be changed


OSD follow Project UX SPEC define
4.White
4.1.Change lighting color to white by APP

4.2.Change brightness by APP or Hot Key with 4 level brightness (0, 30%, 60%, 100%)

Ensure OSD show correct and brightness can be changed


OSD follow Project UX SPEC define
5.Other colors
5.1.Change lighting color by APP,need cover all colors

Exit CUE or uninstall PC Manager/Lenovo vantage/Lenovo Zone app（Please restart system after unistalled app)

Change brightness by Hotkey with 4 level brightness(0,30%,60%,100%)

Ensure OSD show correct and brightness can be changed


OSD follow Project UX SPEC define
Fn key Combination Test (Please skip not support item)
Fn+L/Fn+Prt Scr/Fn+Q/Fn+Up Arrow/Fn+Down Arrow/Fn+Space/Fn+U/Fn+R
If any other Fn combination key is not listed above,please also check its function follow KB lighting SPEC
 
Section : Backlight Mode (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
*Please follow the lastest KB lighting SPEC.

*App setting priority is greater than FW setting, so when you verify FW lighting mode, pls EXIT CUE or uninstall PC Manager/Lenovo Vantage/Lenovo Zone app(Please restart system after uninstall app)
*Equalizer1 & Equalizer2 work when Audio work; If Speakers Muted but Media Player haven’t muted, audio is still work, so lighting is still work too. (If project has different behavior,please confirm and follow the project SPEC or definition)
1.Press the hot key"Fn+space" to change KB backlight mode, need cover all lighting mode.
Ensure all lighting mode shown normally, all lighting mode defined by lasest KB lighting SPEC.

1.1 Press "Fn" key at each mode

Ensure function key LED on and other keys off, LED color is Cool Blue.Function key can refer to Picture 1 in the attachment.


If not support,pls skip; if support,pls follow the lastest KB lighting SPEC.
2.Turn off KB backlight
2.1.Enter Sleep and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is off
2.2.Enter Hibernate and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is off
2.3.Shutdown and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is off
3.Turn on KB backlight
3.1.Enter Sleep and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is on
3.2.Enter Hibernate and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is on
3.3.Shutdown and resume
Ensure KB backlight and Fin lighting is on
 
Section : Audio wave keyboard lighting(If not support,please skip) (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
*Please follow the lastest KB lighting SPEC.
*If "Setting->System->Sound->Sound Control Panel->Speakers Propertis->Advanced->Allow hardware acceleration of audio with this device" is on,support "hardware acceleration of audio" app cannot show audio wave backlight

*Please cover Audio Ripple lighting mode and Audio Bonce lighting mode.


For Yx60:


Audio Ripple lighting mode:KB lighting & U Lighting & Fin Lighting is middle to side.


Audio Bonce lighting mode:KB lighting is from left to right;U Lighting& Fin Lighting is side to side.


For newer than Yx60:


Audio Ripple lighting mode:KB lighting is from left to right;U Lighting& Fin Lighting & Y Logo is side to side.


Audio Bonce lighting mode:KB lighting & U Lighting& Fin Lighting &Y Logo is middle to side.
1--Basic Function

Exit PC Manager/Lenovo vantage/CUE/Lenovo Zone

Press "Fn+space" change backlight to Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode

Ensure keyboard backlight change to Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode

1.Windows Media Player

Playback music by Windows Media Player

If app support "hardware acceleration of audio" , ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode is not work. If not support,ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode can be shown normally and effect can be changed with different frequencies of audio

Adjust system volume

Ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode work normally and effect can be changed with volume

Adjust App volume

Ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode work normally and effect can be changed with volume

Mute system volume

Ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode is not work

Mute App volume

Ensure Audio Ripple/Bonce lighting mode is not work
